Great chapter, but I noticed some small errors

>put your's and Sophia's clothes in the laundry shoot

>*Sophia and your
Two rules in play here; first is that when listing people you always put yourself at the end of the list, and second is that the pronoun should still be grammatically correct even if it was the only one listed, so "your's" doesn't work here. You wouldn't say "you put your's clothes away", would you?
>*chute
It's a laundry chute; same pronunciation, different spelling.
